09/21/82  send_mail request:  reply_to, rpt

Syntax:  rpt {addresses}


Function:  adds addresses to the list of recipients for replies to this
message or prints the contents of the list.


Arguments:
addresses
   are the addresses to add to the list of recipients for replies.
   Type:
         help addresses.gi
   for a description of the syntax of addresses.  If no addresses are
   given, this request prints the list of recipients for replies.


Notes:
If no explicit recipients for replies are specified for the message
either via this request or via use of the -reply_to control argument on
the send_mail command line, read_mail will send replies to this message
to the authors of the message.
